38:04.120 --> 38:06.579
She's not my girlfriend.

38:09.542 --> 38:10.875
What?

38:11.627 --> 38:13.545
I just told her
that you're not my girlfriend.

38:14.130 --> 38:15.588
She probably thinks
you're a prostitute.

38:16.549 --> 38:18.967
Oh, my God. I was wrong.

38:19.093 --> 38:21.386
You're not like Pop, you are Pop.

38:22.263 --> 38:24.222
I should beat you for that.

38:24.432 --> 38:26.266
Exactly like Pop.

38:27.643 --> 38:28.768
Man!

38:44.076 --> 38:46.619
- Sister?
- Mr Morgan.

38:46.746 --> 38:48.246
- Good morning.
- Hi.

38:49.081 --> 38:51.333
I just wanted to apologise
for the other day.

38:51.417 --> 38:54.627
I didn't mean to
come across as indifferent.

38:54.795 --> 38:56.463
Of course not.

38:57.298 --> 39:02.344
The fact is, I'm pretty ignorant
in spiritual matters.

39:02.428 --> 39:05.305
I had a rather
unconventional childhood.

39:06.349 --> 39:09.851
My father taught me
what he thought was important.

39:09.935 --> 39:15.148
But I guess we had some concerns
that seemed more pressing

39:15.274 --> 39:18.193
- than learning about God.
- I see.

39:18.611 --> 39:20.779
But I want Harrison
to have a normal childhood,

39:21.113 --> 39:22.822
a good childhood.

39:23.657 --> 39:25.700
I would like for him to go here.

39:26.660 --> 39:29.204
And you came all the way out here
this morning just to tell me this?

39:31.165 --> 39:33.124
It seemed important.

39:37.713 --> 39:39.339
I'll see if we can find
a place for your son.

39:40.466 --> 39:41.883
Thank you.

40:03.906 --> 40:05.156
Hey.

40:05.699 --> 40:08.034
